idual retirement accounts  annuities  and charitable remainder trusts  represents the means by which they can best balance their desires to help VMI financially and to protect their wealth and that of their families  In the past few years  the VMI Foundation has made an extensive effort to educate members of the VMI Family about how using planned giving can have a mutual benefit to them and to VMI  In conjunction with the VMI Keydet Club  the Foundation established the Washington Arch Society to recognize those alumni and friends who support VMI by using planned gifts  This concerted effort to encourage this form of giving has borne impressive fruit  In the past two fiscal years  2010 and 2011  donors using planned giving made more than  16 6 million in commitments and VMI received more than  8 million in support through realized planned gifts  For further information on how to support VMI using planned giving  please contact  Terrie I  Conrad CFRE Vice President of Planned Giving VMI Foundation 1 800 444 1839  ext  238 Email  tconrad vmiaa Planned Giving For many donors  planned giving  that is the use of such vehicles as bequests  individual retirement accounts  annuities  and charitable remainder trusts  represents the means by which they can best balance their desires to help VMI financially and to protect their wealth and that of their families  In the past few years  the VMI Foundation has made an extensive effort to educate members of the VMI Family about how using planned giving can have a mutual benefit to them and to VMI  In conjunction with the VMI Keydet Club  the Foundation established the Washington Arch Society to recognize those alumni and friends who support VMI by using planned gifts  This concerted effort to encourage this form of giving has borne impressive fruit  In the past two fiscal years  2010 and 2011  donors using planned giving made more than  16 6 million in commitments and VMI received more than  8 million in support through realized pl